        <mxCell id="6PFilM3zcWdMXbaBikjT-14" parent="1" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=none;dashed=1;dashPattern=8 4 1 4;strokeColor=#FF0000;align=left;verticalAlign=top;" value="1. What is SSI? What is the main difference between it and ABZ?&lt;div&gt;2. What is the output of our ADC?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;3. How many shunt resistors for the phases? How do we choose a resistance value? FOC? Low side current sensing? ISSUE: For SimpleFOC, we need to know all 3 current phases, TMC6300 is weird as it bridges current for U and V, not allowing us to separate them. Soln: Inline current sensing instead?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;4. Is there enough current budget? Is there enough torque output? What would be the ADC range?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;5. Can we justly run the motor at 9V? What can we do to step the voltage down?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Grounding in current sense amplifiers&lt;br&gt;https://www.ti.com/lit/an/sboa536/sboa536.pdf?ts=1662480209644&amp;amp;ref_url=https%253A%252F%252Fwww.ti.com%252Fproduct%252FINA240&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Filter ADC inputs w/ low pass&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;https://www.analog.com/en/resources/analog-dialogue/articles/practical-filter-design-precision-adcs.html&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- To prevent aliasing: filter out frequencies &amp;gt;= sample frequency / 2&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5SMsRApsrQQ&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="263.5" width="525" x="-845" y="551.5" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
